{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c836dd54-e7cc-4451-a91c-183d0b92cab3","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # confirm SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # verify it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions. Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/migration) for any breaking changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3774b0a-7654-4be3-a7f8-863ef7f5f684","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files clearly.","outputTokens":339,"requestId":"B907:192B19:183D4E2:1B3984C:69FD403F"},"id":"3b45cfa0-b389-4228-9037-ce3f695f6fef","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:45:43.224Z","parentId":"c321c359-a4d7-49f3-ad8c-177dc3dedb91"}
